values:
I haven't updated since Wednesday and I'd be here for hours if I wrote about each day.

But I'll start with yesterday. It was Friday and I took Maureen's bus home and we hung around her house all night with Mike and Tim. There was poker and pool, gorilla bites?, the classic truth or dare, which turned into truth, seizure dancing, 'good games', and even greater pictures...it was a lot of fun. A lot of fun. And Mike even came out of the closet. (Literally, not figuratively)

Well this morning we got up around noon and hung out..and now me and Mo are at Staci's house. But she's going to work soon, so me and Mo will probably just go back to her house because it's kind of cold outside.

Edit: Alright so, we walked back to Maureen's in the freezing cold and just hung around with the bubby-loving babies till I left around 11. <3

Alright well, school's going okay. We can't talk english in la clase de espanol anymore and even though it's going to be hard, I think it will be fun. I can't believe it's Wednesday already. Hm, nothing really interesting happened today, except that Kelsi fainted, Jimmy broke his nose, Britt was in tears, and my arm is severely bruised. Alright, so the first part of that sentence was sarcasm. It was a very interesting day. Most of the junior class got their blood drawn for a lipid profile. We all had to fast since 8 last night; so by the time we got to school we were all starving. Kelsi, Melissa, and I were scheduled to get our blood drawn at 8:30, and by the time we were weighed and measured and our blood pressure was taken, it was about 9. So finally the three of us were in line to get our blood taken; and I was so scared. Kelsi was first, then Melissa, and finally me. Well, when I got behind the curtains, Kelsi was lying on a mat and was as white as a ghost, so I thought she had already passed out, but the nurses figured it would be best for her to lie down, that way if she did faint she wouldn't fall over in the chair. Just as the nurse is done pulling the needle out of me, Kelsi hits the floor. I thought she slammed her head into a table..but thankfully she only hit the ground. Anyway, they had to snap one of those ammonia sticks to wake her up and the hilarious part is...she didnt know she fainted. We all ate, well they ate, I gorged myself with poptarts, cinnamin buns, and apple juice. And the drama ended there, or so we thought...

So before lunch, Meliss comes running up to me at my locker, and starts rambling about Jimmy fainting after he got his blood taken and getting rushed to the hospital and Britt crying, and I'm thinking that this is one of Melissa and Jimmy's schemes to make me believe something they totally made up. So I'm like, "Yeah right. I don't believe you." But, then she started getting convincing, so I believed her. Andd turns out Jimmy did faint and hit his face head on, had a seizure and broke his nose! He was passed out for like 3 minutes! I felt so bad for him. Well I called him after school and he's going to go to school tomorrow. Geez, if I broke my nose, I'd milk it for all it's worth. I wouldn't come to school until my nose had made a full recovery and you could never tell it was broken.

So, of course we lost the game on Friday. But atleast we had a good time. Melissa came over right after school and we hung out until we left for the game with Tiffani. We met up with Maureen and watched the game, but it wasn't long until we were bored. We walked around and ran into Rachel and then me and Rachel came across Ashley and Brandon, so it was a cute little Costa's reunion. Hmm. Well after the game, Meliss drove me home, but we think it would have been cooler if she had her license.

I went to Maureen's on Saturday. And we did a ton of walking. We probably lost atleast 5 pounds. I got there, and we got bored right away, so we went for a walk. We met up with some guys and walked to the park with them. We really didn't want to be there with them, and thank the Lord, that Tim called Maureen. We made up an excuse that we were going to hang out with our other friends, so we finally got to leave. We walked straight to Maureen's house to cover the stench of the cigarette's that the guys were smoking...and then we went back down to town, to find something to eat. It was really humid out so we figured that icecream was a good solution. After that, we met up with Mike and Tim at the Chinese place. And after that we all went to Tim's. But before me and Mo could get there, one of boys we met on the way to the park spotted us. How annoying. Well we hung out at Tim's for a little bit, but Maureen I got bored, so we went back to her house, ate some food, and then went back down to Tim's. A little while later, Mike and Tim were going to watch a soccer game so me and Mo left for her house a final time. We hung out with Mary for a while and then watched the babies for a little bit. And when Mike got home we had a hilarious time, laughing at the pictures and videos. I left around 10ish and went straight to bed. It was a long, exhausting day.

And, all I've done today, is gone to Walmart, but I'm really tired. So I think I'm just going to finish some homework and go to bed.

So I think you all deserve a decent update. And since I had fun today, I'll write about that. Well, I woke up this morning, and was running late since I really did not feel like getting up early. But when I got to school, everything was alright. Spanish was review work; Wellness was so very boring; Chem was long, and then she tried to get us to start a lab 10 minutes before class was over; and english was boring and going over homework and the rest of our introductions.

 Well after school was the fun part of my day. I went to Staci's around 3:30 and we walked to Maureen's. You might need to be reminded, that this is a long hilly walk and it was veryy-very hot. We got there and hung out with the little kids and took lots and lots of pichassss. <333. Then we thought we'd walk to the library to get some homework done, but you know how that goes...it's a struggle to leave Mo's house, the kids beg us to stay... Well, we got there around 6:30 but the library closes at 5. Nice job. But I don't mind, none of us were in the mood to do homework anyway. So on the way back to Maureen's we stop at Joe and Lorenzo's and ate there. And took more pictures. Haha. After a full mean, we walk back to Maureen's, and stay and chat for a bit, and then me and Staci walk all the way back to her house. And her mom took me home around 8. Andd, then my parent's weren't too pleased, because I was supposed to be home at 6, so I can eat dinner with them...but oh well.

Well, Laguna is starting now...and I still want to put pictures up so, I'll give you a link soon.

Guess what I bought at Best Buy yesterday. Guess. I bought a digicam.. as in digital camera. Andd a 20gb iPod. My dad split the cost of the ipod with me, because he's going to use it too. But I'm so happy I finally got them. I've wanted a digital camera for so long and an iPod since before I can remember.

After coming home from Scranton, I went straight to the bowling alley with Melissa. And we met up with Kelsi, Jimmy, and Staci. Andd took lots of pictures <3. Which I will put up soon; hopefully.

Now, I have to read Pride and Prejudice up to Chapter 23. Wanna know where I am? Like page 10.

CONGRATULATIONS TO BRITTY D! [she got her permit] (okay and by britty d, i mean, britt martinez, but ya know her middle name starts with a d, so it rhymes..i just didnt want you to think i meant a different britt.)

Yesterday was the first day of school and we're juniors this year, so we got the "junior year" speech about how colleges look at this year and it's the hardest academic year; and we better start looking at colleges; and blah de blah. And Dr.Hudak also talked about the construction and parking and ya know, the basic rules and first day speech.

Speaking of construction, the hallways are packed full of people, and now that we cant use that lakeside hallway, its just too crowded. But my schedule is pretty good and goes like this:

Spanish IV: I have Mrs.Petrillo, and I loved her in Spanish II, so thats good. And Melissa and Britt are with me <3
Grad Project on A days: This class is really going to suck. I have basically no one to talk to and I really don't know what I'm going to do.
Gym/Health on B days: This is pretty much my grad proj class. I really don't know who I'll partner with. Ugh, I don't talk to anyone really.
A lunch: This is a good lunch, I sit with my soulsister Britt.
Chemistry: Maureen sits next to me and she is my lab partner <33
British Lit Honors: I've got a good class there too, and Melissa's there. But I still haven't read my summer reading. Uh oh.

So right after school yesterday, I went to Salina's to babysit, and stayed there till about 10. So that sucked, and then I had to come home and read some stuff for Chem.

And tomorrow is the first friday, but I'm working so I haven't got any other plans. And Salina will probably call me for Saturday, so there pretty much goes my weekend...

have you ___________ this summer 2005? SURVEY

had a party? mm, not a party party.
been to a party? nah.
spent the night with a friend? oh definatly.
laughed until your stomach hurt? oh yes.
gone on a vacation? mhm.
tanned? Of course! What an insulting question. Of course, I tanned. Who hasn't?!
went to a camp? nuh uh.
swam? it wouldn't be summer without swimming.
went to the movies? yes. this summer I saw, Wedding Crashers and Red-Eye. Both starring Rachel <3
gone shopping? yesss another, of course.
are you even out of school? yes, and sadly we go back tomorrow.
gotten freakishly bored? not freakishly..what the heck is freakishly bored.
have you gotten sun burned? i don't burn; i get tan.
made a bonfire? oh meliss, we never did.
been outside during a lightning storm? on the porch, mehbeh.
been to another country? um no.
been to the the hospital with an injury? oh thank the lord i have not.
commited a crime/broken the law? not this summer. ;o)
stole anything? who me steal?! you have got to be kidding.
gone on a road trip? does driving to florida count?
had sex? nope
been to a concert? KELLY CLARKSON BIOTCH! <3 with my ladies..and jimmy. [ohh 8-7-05; i miss you]
had a memorable moment? ^^ and some other ones of course.
had a horrible moment? maybe;
made new friends? yes, i have.
thought about school? being as it starts tomorrow, you can say i have.
been to the beach? oh fo' sho.
thought about a someone special? ;o) wouldn't you like to know.
had the best time of your life this summer or other summers? eh, it was nothing too special. but i loved it nontheless.

I know I've said it tons of times, but I can't say it enough: I love the Keane Family. So I headed to Maureen's yesterday after work and we hung out there with the family till about 8. Kelly and I were having an in-depth conversation about Chuckie (that freaky doll from the movie) and Charlie (from Hide and Seek) and she was telling me a story of  how one time Chuckie was in John and Matt's closet and she was sitting on the bed and she heard a noise and she said to herself, "holy friggen crap, what the hell was that?!" and I was hysterical laughing because it's just too funny to hear these words coming out of a six-year-old's mouth. And she's dead serious about it too, which can be a little freaky sometimes. Later on Maureen's dad took Maureen, Mike, Ed, Joe, Patrick, and me to the new Pizza Hut. It was really nice and the food still tasted the same. And that's good, because I would have died if they changed anything about the wings <3333. After pizza and wings, we went to the halfway house for icecream and headed home.

So this morning, I was awoken by Kelly turning on the light and jumping into bed and before I know it; all of the little ones (Kelly, Kimmy, Matt, and John) have swarmed into the room. So for an hour or so, we just entertained them and watched Rachel too. Then around noon, we all left for L.A. (as in Lake Adventure). We spent most of the day there just hanging out in the club house and talking to everyone that vacations there and such.

And now I'm home; sulking because I reallyy have to read my summer reading. I got my schedule yesterday and I have english 4th block; first semester. And all I've read is my choice book. Geez, why do I wait till the last minute?! And speaking of waiting till the last minute, I'm finishing shopping tomorrow before I have to babysit at 3. Which means I have to get up early to be at the mall when they open. Ugh.

It is September 1st. What is that?! Where did summer go? There's only 7 days left, and that makes me sad.

Alright well, I worked 10-4 yesterday, and it was so slow. After work, Maureen called to see if I wanted to hangout. So around 9, Maureen, Staci, Mike, Tim, and I went bowling till they closed at 11. 

I worked at golf today and I love working outside, it's just a lot easier. The golf team stopped by, and since like half the golf team works at Costa's...I just kept handing out free baskets to most of the guys. But when they left, my manager told me to make sure I was only handing out free baskets to employees..which I was...pretty much.

Tomorrow, I have to get up early so I can go with Kaylene to freshman orientation cause she wants me to show her around. And then work at 10. And after work, probably hanging out with Staci and Maureen.

Sunday was the MTV Video Music Awards so Britt, Melissa, Kaylene, Tim, Joe, and Staci came over. Anddddd Jimmy was invited, but aw, he had to ice his ankle, so he couldn't come. The VMA's were stupid this year, and Mariah Carey was a fat cow as usual. I heard she ripped out all the size 12 tags on her jeans and sewed in size 6's. HOW PATHETIC. Jennifer Lopez wasn't even at the VMA's so that sucked. But Kelly won 2 awards, and performed last...and they always save the best for last..even though she didnt perform as well as she usually does. But it was fun at the house. 

The girls stayed over and we went bed really late and then had to get up at 7; so we'd be at dorney when they opened. So everyone was really tired. When we got there the weather wasn't that bad, it's was kind of hazy and hot. I actually went on Talon and Hydra, my first "loopies". And the pictures were hilarious. We did some water rides and on one ride there was a lady with man feet. Ugh gross. By the time we had to go everyone was extremely exhausted, and everyone fell asleep on the way home. Overall the day was really fun.

Today, my boss called at 9:30 to tell me that Costa's wouldn't be opening today. So I'll probably just hang around the house and procrastinate against my summer reading. (Is that even how you use that word, I don't think so, it sounds really weird.)

Last night I saw Red Eye with Staci and it was soooooo good. <3 I love Rachel McAdams.

So I worked from 11-4 today. And it was Red Barons Day and a few players dropped by for a few hours and signed autographs and took pictures and hung out with the kids at baseball. It was pretty busy but I worked with Rachel so we had a good time.

Got home and get a call from Maureen asking if I wanted to go bowling tonight with Tim Sils and Joey B. But Maureen wasn't back from dropping her sister off at ESU. So the boys came here and we hung out for a while and then we went bowling. Maureen stilllll wasnt back yet. So we stayed at the bowling alley a little while longer...played some pool and then left because Maureen didn't have a ride.

Tomorrow I work 11-5ish and then I'm having a little VMA party. HA. With Meliss, Stace, Britt, Kay, and Jimmy Jimmy Jimbo. And maybe Tim and Joe'll stop by. And then Monday it's Dorney with the girlieeesss whom I love. <3333

I worked 3 hours on Friday, and finally found out why there are such things as a 3 hour shift...it's to cover people who are on breaks. So I worked outside at baseball and then golf. I like working golf a lot better, because I dont know how to work baseball... I just give out change. And at golf, it's less lonely..

After work, I went straight to Staci's. We watched a movie, and ate super spicy wings...they were burning my mouth and bringing tears to my eyes and I look over at Staci and she's practically swallowing them without a care in the world. Now, Staci has tears in her eyes because she's laughing so hard as I jug down about a gallon of water.

We woke up early the next morning, so Maureen could pick us up, and then we went to the mall. Have I mentioned how much I love her little brothers and sisters? They're just too fricken adorable. Maureen, Staci, and I shopped from the mall opened, until 3. You would think that would be enough time, but we're still not done. After that, I hung out Maureen's and then she came over here...we ate and hung out, took pictures by the black light (<3) and watched The Notebook. Took her home, since she had work in the morning.

Today I slept late, which I haven't done in oh-so-very long and I've just been lounging around the house ever since. I go to work at 5 and leave at 9. So that's gonna suck. And tomorrow, I have off. I work 2 days this week, so I'm hoping I can go to the mall again or something. Next Sunday are the VMA's so I made sure I wasn't working that night, because Staci, Melissa, and Kaylene are coming over to watch and sleepover and the following day we're all going to Dorney Park And after that, it's like 10 days left of summer. TEN. That's all, and I haven't even started Wuthering Heights and Pride and Prejudice. But I have spanish first with Britt and Melissa, so I'm looking forward to that.

Babysitting last night was AWFUL! Ugh, horrendous. I watched all four of the kids, ages: 2 months, 2 years, 3 years, and 6 years old. The girls, (the 2 and 3 year old) are supposed to be in bed by 7, 7:30. I got there at 7 and they were still awake, the baby was crying so I couldn't get the girls to bed at the same time. Finally I get the baby to be quiet. But the girls wouldn't go to bed. And it wasn't until 10:30 that everyone went to sleep. Then I didnt get home till about 2:30, and didnt fall asleep till 3:30.

I woke up at 10 today, and couldnt fall back to sleep; I layed out in the sun, but it was just too hot. Came inside, showered, and hung out till I had to go work at 4. Work was unbelievably hot. We have air conditioning but it was busy, so with the doors constintly opening, it wasn't really cool inside. Then it got really dark, and windy, and it was lightning and thundering and baboom, the power went out for like 5 seconds.. It started pouring and everything outside closed. We were really slow...so I just hung outside for awhile, getting paid to do nothing.

I work tomorrow, 6-9, but really what's the point of going in, just so I can work for 3 lousy hours...

hokay so. Yesterday I worked from 10-4. I came home and that night me and Staci went to walmart. Todayy, I worked 10-4. And I worked for like an hour at golf...and I hit a golfball. I've never done that except for gym class..and so the guys were telling me, that I atleast had to try to hit one, I missed..like 3 times and then I finally got it. But whoopdiedoo.

I'm babysitting tomorrow. Like all day..not kidding. I'm babysitting from 9:30-6 for one family. And then around 9 or 10; I'll babysitting for another family till probably around 1 or 2 in the morning. Kay, then I work Sunday, Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday, Thursday, Friday, and Saturday. But the hours are lousy, some of those days, it's like 3 or 4 hours. What is that? Huh?! What's the point?

and it reallyy looks like it's gonna pour any minute..so i better go shut some windows

I can't laugh because my stomach still hurts from screaming at the concert.

School starts in less than a month. But it looks like they might not be done with all the construction by September 7th.

I went to the fair tonight with Melissa. We met Staci and we just did a few rides and ate and got airbrushed tatoos <3. It was...fun..but at the same time boring. Does that make sense?

My throat is absolutly killing me after last night's Kelly Clarkson concert. It was soo muchh fun. She was soo good. Soooo soo soo good. Just as good as the cd. I wishh I could go back again. Ughh; I can't tell you how good it was.  Staci, Melissa, Britt and I just kept screaming. I didn't hear Jimmy scream or even sing. But it seemed like he had a good time. Haha. When it got quiet I would just scream again. "AHHHHHH!!!!!!!!! GO KELLYY! WHOOOOOOO!!!!!!!" My stomach aches from screaming so hard.  Ohhh, lord, it was tooo much fun. The Graham Colton band opened for her and they were really good too. We couldn't understand much of the words, but they were pretty good.  After the show, I bought a poster of Kelly. And the Graham Colton band was there to sign autographs and such, soo they signed the back of my poster. After all that we slept at Melissa's and that was really fun too. We played taboo and it was hilarious.

I was supposed to work today, but with the rain...i didn't have to go in.....

anywayyy, i'm really tired. i think i'm gonna watch a movie or something..

Since I have nothing better to do on my day off, I went to Costa's with Staci. We played mini golf (which I haven't done FOR-EVER) for free. Twice, I got a hole in one...andd one was in luckyyy 13. It was extremely hot out. We stopped inside for a drink and went in the arcade for a while. That was fun. Chatted with Carolina and Rachie for a little. Then we went on the go-carts..for free. I had the faster cart but I let Staci get ahead for a little..just to be nice. Staci didn't know where her brakes were..so when we had to stop she nearly ran over Brandon and stopped in the middle of the track. Hilarious. Inside for some ice-cream andd back out to the go-carts..for free. This time I had thee crappy-est one there. Wayyy slow and I thought the tires were like gonna come off. Staci almost lapped me, but with my swerving she wasn't able to..We left a while later and went for a quick ride on her boat. Dipped our feet in the water, and a fish decided Staci's toe might make a good meal..she nearly gave me a heart attack..and I refused to put my feet back in for a while. After that we ate at Crazy Fingers..which is where Staci works. The wings were really good. But our conversation was too much. And I nearly died when I heard "there'll be eleven". ;op

Work was absolutely horrendous today. We had 300 campers. We ran out of food-order numbers; and we had to write down names. The soda machine wasn't working half the time. The campers were rude and snobby.  It was just awful. But I'm off till next week.

I'm babysitting tomorrow morning..and probably just hanging out tomorrow night.

Lately my entries have been really small and boring..but what are ya gonna do? which reminds me...

Yesterday, morning I went to Staci's and we watched Billy Madison. Funny. Then we walked down (in the sweltering heat) to Joe and Lorenzo's and ate some cheese fries and warm soda. Then we walked back to Staci's house (again in the heat; and the walk from Mo's to Staci's is not close.)  Danielle (Staci's sister) and Staci were ahead and they locked us out of the house (Me: "OH MY GOD! LET US INTO THIS HOUSE; BEFORE WE HAVE A HEATSTROKE!!!") so we had to run around to the kitchen before they had a chance to lock that door too. Then it was a mad dash to stand in front of the air conditioner. Funny stuff. Then we watched Never Been Kissed.  After that me and Maureen told Staci we'd meet her later, and we walked back to Maureen's. And let me tell you, the cutest, funniest kids live there.  So we walk into the house, and Maureen's older sister (Mary) is yelling at Maureen's 6 year old sister (Kelly):
Mary: "KELLY, IF YOU EVER FRICKEN DO THAT AGAIN, I'LL FRICKEN PULL YOUR HAIR OUT!"
Kelly: "Shut up."
...like it didn't even phase her. Well, I definatly found that funny.
Then, an even younger sister pulls down a picture from the refrigerator, she says to me, "that's Ed. that's Mike." (pointing to 2 of the boys) "Ed thinks this is Mike....he's an idiot" And I was hysterical. It was thee funniest thing ever.
I saw the new baby, and she's adorable.  We left with 3 of the boys; but not before Matt gave me a cute little hug. I love him; soo cute.

We met back up with Staci, her sister, and her sister's friend, and all 8 of us, headed to that stupid Hawley carnival. I didn't go on many rides because I refuse to go on anything that goes backwards. A slice of pizza, a bottle of water, a funnel cake, a powdered sugar fight, and about 20 dollars later, it was time, for one-last-ride. So everyone but, me and 3 of Maureen's brothers got on that stupid backwards wheel, while I felt sick, and we'll say "ruined a chance"?

After the carnival, me, Staci, and her sister and her friend, walked back to Staci's house (notice this is the 4th trip I've made.) and her mom drove me home.

Overall, the day was fun, a night to remember, and let's hope that we all get together again, and have a blast.

Ah dios mio.  5 days of school left. 5. I remember sitting in math last semester, watching the TV say 75 days gone bye, (yes it says bye), and thinking, GAH this school year can't go by quickly enough. But HELLO, where has the time gone now?  I also remember last August when Carolina only had 30 days left of summer before she went to KU, and now school year's over for her...

But, I'm excited for summer. I love the summer. I love the heat, I love BBQ's, I love vacationing, I love my job (okay, maybe I'm getting a little carried away with that..), but I love every minute of my summer, and this summer is going to be the best.  Except for the fact that my sunshine Britt, will be gone for the first half or so.

Coming back from the primary school after peer helping today:

I am the first one in the van so I go to the very last row, and slide alllll the way over.  Melissa's next. She slides in right next to me.  Then two other kids fit in with us...so I'm squished into the window. I casually turn my head towards the window, and screeeam, "MOVE OVER!! EVERYONE! MOVE OVER!"  I slide so far over into Melissa that the kid at the end of the seat, slides off onto the floor of the van..but I don't care, because there is a wasp on the window.  And, I know that I will get stung.  Melissa has no idea what's going on, until she sees the wasp, being my friend, she understands and doesnt make me sit near the window, but that doesnt solve the problem of the kid on the floor, so I scrunch down inbetween the sits, so Melissa may move closer to the window and the kid can get off the floor.  I think everyone on the van thinks I'm crazy, but atleast I wasn't stung.

The moral of this story........drumroll puhlease........don't sit by the window in the backseat of a van.
